SIMPLE: sufflaminate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sufflaminate
<hw>Suf*flam"i*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sufflaminatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>sufflaminare</ets> to hold back
by a clog, from <ets>sufflamen</ets> a clog.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
retard the motion of, as a carriage, by preventing one or more of its
wheels from revolving, either by means of a chain or otherwise.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to stop; to impede.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sufflate</ent>⟦br⟧
